         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// elephant's tusk • <hi>Sanskrit</hi> ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// from that one • <hi>Sanskrit</hi> • to that one ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// either the root • <hi>Sanskrit</hi> ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// having seized compassion towards oneself /// </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// <hi>Sanskrit</hi> • he separates • <hi>Sanskrit</hi> he open(s) ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// worthy of ... • <hi>Sanskrit</hi> • without ... ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// even that (f. sg.) as little possessions (?) ... ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// having removed  his own estate ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// the ones reaching ... • <hi>Sanskrit</hi>   </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// he may generate <hi>Sanskrit</hi> • having taken refuge ///</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">Note that the recto and verso of the fragment <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a463"/> have to be reversed, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1967"/><citedRange>163</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">The little fragment PK NS 516 completes the fragment PK NS 13 on the left side. The resulting fragment belongs to the middle part of a leaf including the right part of the string hole. The fragment belongs to a leaf of the same manuscript to which <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkns12"/> belongs. The text contains Tocharian B translations of words and phrases of the Śrāmaṇyaphalasūtra. Some of them have parallels in Tocharian A, namely <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a460"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a466"/>, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/>.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/> a3.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/> a4.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/> b2.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="lingcomment">The form <hi>puttaṅgaṃ</hi> is a misspelling for <hi>puttaṅkäṃ</hi> as translation of Skt. <hi>vibhajati</hi> and it matches Tocharian A <hi>putäṅkāṣ</hi> as restored in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/> b4.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/> b4.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a461"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a465"/> b5.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">The <hi>nt</hi>-participle <hi>yänmāṣṣeñcaṃ</hi> shows the late form of the nominative plural ending instead of standard <hi>-añ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a463"/> a4 ‹ b4.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">The form <hi>(ta)nmaṣṣitär</hi> is 3sg middle of the Kausativ of the root <hi>täm-</hi> 'to produce', cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:malzahn2010"/><citedRange>653</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment" subtype="Correspondences_in_Tocharian_A">This line corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a463"/> a5 ‹ b5.</note></p>
         </div>
